Browse available RBA data series

Source: R/browse_data.R
browse_rba.Rd

Browse available RBA data series

browse_rba_series(search_string = "")

browse_rba_tables(search_string = "")

Arguments

search_string

Word or phrase to search for, such as "gold" or "commodity" or "labour". If left as "", the function will return all series.

Value

A data.frame (tbl_df) containing RBA data series/tables that match the search_string.

Examples


# Find series that contain 'unemployment'
browse_rba_series("unemployment")

#> # A tibble: 2 x 7
#>   table_no series   series_id series_type   table_title cur_hist description

#> 2 H5       Unemplo… GLFSURSA  Seasonally a… H5 Labour … current  Unemployed per…
